    "name": "Question 18 @ 2017/2018",
    "Question": {
      "content": "In converting galvanometer into an ammeter, which of the following is correct?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "A shunt Rs is connected in parallel with the galvanometer",
        "A multiplier is connected in parallel with the galvanometer",
        "A shunt, Rs is connected in series with the galvanometer",
        "A multiplier is connected in series with the galvanometer"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "A shunt Rs is connected in parallel with the galvanometer"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "To convert a galvanometer into an ammeter, a low-resistance shunt (Rs) is connected in parallel to allow most current to bypass the galvanometer, extending its range."
    },
